  "response_text": "{\n\"leaf_scores\": [\n{\n\"leaf\": \"Algorithmic_Transparency_Requirement_Support\",\n\"score\": 298,\n\"confidence\": 0.62,\n\"reasoning\": \"The person's high openness and low agreeableness, combined with a libertarian anti-censorship orientation, provide moderate resistance to the spam-driven ad-manipulation operation, but the sustained AI-generated content erodes trust in transparency mandates slightly.\"\n},\n{\n\"leaf\": \"Bot_And_Inauthentic_Behaviour_Disclosure_Support\",\n\"score\": 441,\n\"confidence\": 0.58,\n\"reasoning\": \"High conscientiousness and a strong preference for order make the person somewhat receptive to the operation's narrative that disclosure is ineffective, but their very high extraversion and social network size limit the movement as they value authentic interaction.\"\n},\n{\n\"leaf\": \"Civic_Media_Literacy_Education_Support\",\n\"score\": 609,\n\"confidence\": 0.55,\n\"reasoning\": \"The operation's focus on ad-manipulation and model-reputation pressure does not directly target media literacy, and the person's high openness and internal political efficacy keep this belief largely stable with only a small downward drift.\"\n},\n{\n\"leaf\": \"Counter_Disinformation_Agency_Support\",\n\"score\": -201,\n\"confidence\": 0.65,\n\"reasoning\": \"Very low trust in government and institutions, combined with high anti-egalitarianism and a competitive worldview, makes the person highly susceptible to the operation's narrative that such agencies are tools of elite control, moving them further into opposition.\"\n},\n{\n\"leaf\": \"Cross_Border_Foreign_Media_Restriction_Support\",\n\"score\": -426,\n\"confidence\": 0.60,\n\"reasoning\": \"High ethnic nationalism and national identification are initially at odds with the operation's goal, but the person's low trust in institutions and high collective narcissism allow the spam-driven narrative of foreign manipulation to deepen their opposition to restrictions.\"\n},\n{\n\"leaf\": \"Cross_Platform_Researcher_Data_Access_Support\",\n\"score\": 264,\n\"confidence\": 0.57,\n\"reasoning\": \"The operation's AI-agentic architecture and model-reputation pressure subtly undermine the perceived legitimacy of independent researchers, and the person's low agreeableness and high libertarianism make them skeptical of data-sharing mandates.\"\n},\n{\n\"leaf\": \"Freedom_From_Content_Moderation_Preference\",\n\"score\": 548,\n\"confidence\": 0.61,\n\"reasoning\": \"The operation's goal aligns perfectly with the person's very high libertarianism, anti-censorship orientation, and low authoritarianism, so the spam-driven narrative that moderation is censorship amplifies their pre-existing preference.\"\n},\n{\n\"leaf\": \"Government_Funding_For_Open_Source_Trust_Tools_Support\",\n\"score\": -103,\n\"confidence\": 0.63,\n\"reasoning\": \"Very low trust in government and high system-justification skepticism make the person receptive to the operation's implication that government-funded tools are co-opted, moving them from mild opposition to clearer opposition.\"\n},\n{\n\"leaf\": \"Independent_Fact_Checking_Ecosystem_Support\",\n\"score\": 374,\n\"confidence\": 0.56,\n\"reasoning\": \"The operation's ad-manipulation and model-reputation pressure cast doubt on fact-checking independence, and the person's low trust in science and experts, combined with high openness, allows a moderate downward revision.\"\n},\n{\n\"leaf\": \"Online_Political_Advertising_Transparency_Support\",\n\"score\": 487,\n\"confidence\": 0.59,\n\"reasoning\": \"The operation's core mechanism of ad-manipulation directly undermines faith in transparency, and the person's high conscientiousness and low agreeableness make them question the effectiveness of such mandates, leading to a clear but not extreme reduction.\"\n},\n{\n\"leaf\": \"Platform_Accountability_Regulation_Support\",\n\"score\": -248,\n\"confidence\": 0.64,\n\"reasoning\": \"Very low trust in institutions and high libertarianism make the person highly receptive to the operation's narrative that regulation is a power grab, moving them from moderate opposition to stronger opposition.\"\n},\n{\n\"leaf\": \"Public_Service_Broadcasting_Funding_Support\",\n\"score\": -326,\n\"confidence\": 0.60,\n\"reasoning\": \"The operation's model-reputation pressure and spam delivery erode trust in all institutional media, and the person's low trust in government and high ethnic nationalism amplify this, deepening their opposition to public funding.\"\n},\n{\n\"leaf\": \"Recommender_System_Choice_Mandate_Support\",\n\"score\": 153,\n\"confidence\": 0.55,\n\"reasoning\": \"The operation's AI-agentic architecture subtly frames choice mandates as ineffective, and the person's high openness and low agreeableness make them slightly more skeptical, but their libertarian streak limits the movement.\"\n},\n{\n\"leaf\": \"Synthetic_Media_Labelling_Mandate_Support\",\n\"score\": 398,\n\"confidence\": 0.57,\n\"reasoning\": \"The operation's use of AI-generated content and model-reputation pressure directly challenges the efficacy of labelling, and the person's low trust in institutions and high openness allow a moderate reduction in support.\"\n},\n{\n\"leaf\": \"Trust_In_Mainstream_Journalism\",\n\"score\": -192,\n\"confidence\": 0.66,\n\"reasoning\": \"The operation's sustained spam and ad-manipulation campaign, combined with the person's already very low trust in science and experts and high collective narcissism, further erodes their minimal trust in mainstream journalism.\"\n},\n{\n\"leaf\": \"Whistleblower_Protections_For_Platform_Researchers_Support\",\n\"score\": 331,\n\"confidence\": 0.58,\n\"reasoning\": \"The operation's narrative that researchers are biased or co-opted by platforms resonates with the person's low trust in institutions and high anti-egalitarianism, leading to a small but clear reduction in support.\"\n},\n{\n\"leaf\": \"Foreign_Information_Manipulation_Transparency_Mandate_Support\",\n\"score\": 275,\n\"confidence\": 0.59,\n\"reasoning\": \"The operation's focus on foreign manipulation and model-reputation pressure aligns with the person's high ethnic nationalism, but their low trust in government makes them skeptical of mandates, resulting in a modest downward movement.\"\n},\n{\n\"leaf\": \"Government_Distrust_Of_Elections\",\n\"score\": -608,\n\"confidence\": 0.67,\n\"reasoning\": \"The operation's spam-driven narrative of systemic manipulation strongly reinforces the person's already very low trust in government and institutions, moving them from strong distrust to even stronger distrust of electoral integrity.\"\n}\n]\n}",
